:QUOTE
The oldest sleep aid is a handful of dried plants. That is not a metaphor. That is the recipe.

:INFO
What Herbs Are Used and Why
Lavender essential oil has the most peer-reviewed evidence for reducing sleep onset latency — the time it takes to fall asleep. Hops (Humulus lupulus) dried flower cones contain dimethyl vinyl carbinol, shown to reduce nocturnal activity. Mugwort is traditionally associated with vivid dreams in European and Native American herbalism. Chamomile adds a calming, sweet scent. Combined in a small pillow tucked under the sleeping pillow, the warmth from your head activates the volatile aromatics.

:COUNTER.half
1 Cup Lavender
Core filling for a standard sleep pillow size
|
:COUNTER.half
3 to 6 Months
Useful lifespan before herbs need refreshing or replacing

:PATH
Gather and Dry the Herbs
Harvest or buy herbs at peak oil content and dry completely before use.
|
:INFO
Gather and Dry the Herbs
Use dried herbs only — fresh herbs mold in a sealed pillow. Buy culinary-grade dried lavender, dried hops cones, dried chamomile, and dried mugwort from a bulk herb supplier or natural foods store. If harvesting lavender yourself, cut before the flowers fully open and dry hanging in a dark, ventilated space for 2 weeks.

:PATH
Blend the Herbs
Mix herbs in a bowl and add a few drops of lavender essential oil.
|
:INFO
Blend the Herbs
Combine 1 cup dried lavender, 1/2 cup dried hops cones, 1/4 cup dried chamomile, and 1/4 cup dried mugwort in a bowl. Add 5 to 10 drops of lavender essential oil to boost and fix the scent. Mix gently. Let the blend rest in a sealed container for 24 hours before filling the pillow — this allows the essential oil to absorb into the dried material evenly.

:PATH
Sew the Pillow Cover
Sew a small envelope-style cotton cover — roughly 6 by 8 inches.
|
:INFO
Sew the Pillow Cover
Cut two pieces of tightly woven cotton fabric (muslin or cotton lawn) each 7 by 9 inches. Place right sides together. Sew three sides with a 1/2-inch seam allowance. Turn right side out. Fill loosely with the herb blend — about 1 cup of dried herbs. Fold in the seam allowance on the open end and sew shut by hand or machine.

:CHECKLIST
Herb Blend Ingredients
[ ] 1 cup dried lavender flowers
[ ] 1/2 cup dried hops cones
[ ] 1/4 cup dried chamomile flowers
[ ] 1/4 cup dried mugwort
[ ] 5 to 10 drops lavender essential oil
[ ] Cotton muslin or lawn fabric for the cover

:NOTE
Refresh with Essential Oil as Scent Fades
The volatile aromatics in dried herbs dissipate over 3 to 6 months. Before discarding the herbs, add 5 drops of lavender essential oil through the seam and squeeze the pillow to distribute — this extends the useful life by another 2 to 3 months. Replace herbs entirely once the material no longer releases scent when squeezed.

:QUOTE
You will notice it is missing more than you notice when it is there. That is what effective interventions feel like.

